 English <i>fugol</i> ‘fowl, bird’). Alternatively, a nickname from Middle English <i>fughel</i>, <i>foghel</i>, <i>foul</i> ‘fowl, bird’, either with reference to physical appearance, size, or behavior, or possibly also a nickname for someone who kept or sold birds.","Americanized form of German   Faul  ."]}]},{"name":"Simon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Simon Felton was born about 1265, in West Felton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Felton. He had at least 1 daughter with Hawise Strange."},"et":{"Abt 1265–":"umbes 1265–Surnud","1253–Male":"1253–Surnud","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1285–1316":"1285–1316","1272–1354":"1272–1354","1235–1315":"1235–1315","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","Abt 1272":"umbes 1272","1235":"1235","Abt 1265":"umbes 1265","1354":"1354","1265":"1265","1253":"1253","1285":"1285","1272":"1272","Baconsthorpe, Norfolk, England":"Baconsthorpe, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","West Felton, Oswestry, Shropshire, England":"West Felton, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1265–":"noin 1265–Kuollut","1253–Male":"1253–Kuollut","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1285–1316":"1285–1316","1272–1354":"1272–1354","1235–1315":"1235–1315","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","A